<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,819,1024]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,385,819,844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Material examined.</emphasis>
Two females from Islas Marietas (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[945,1005,820,844]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="9339.0">9339</number>
), two females from Zacatoso (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[220,280,855,879]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="9341.0">9341</number>
B), and two males from Estacahuite (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[854,915,855,879]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="9347.0">9347</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,819,1024]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,892,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was noted as endemic to the Gulf of California (Brusca 
<number box="[1105,1165,892,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="1980.0">1980</number>
), though recently it was recorded in the Huatulco region (García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu-Sánchez 
<number box="[939,1000,927,951]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="2009.0">2009</number>
). In our study we confirm the presence of the species out of the Gulf of California and provided several sites along the Mexican Tropical Pacific coast, from Islas Marietas to the Huatulco region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
